    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan and break it up with a wooden spoon</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>chestnut</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> into the pan and cook for 5 min or until the sausage meat is beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the sausage meat is beginning to brown, grate the <strong>peeled garlic</strong> into the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>orzo</strong>,<strong> </strong>stirring to coat the grains and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>and<strong> Dijon mustard</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked with a slight bite and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked through, increase the heat to medium-high and add your <strong>creme fraiche</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>one pan creamy sausage, mushroom & spinach orzo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-creamy-sausage-mushroom-and-spinach-orzo-with-side-and-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pan creamy sausage, mushroom & spinach orzo </strong>and<strong> </strong>grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> finely all over top</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
